cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.NA, cs.GT, cs.IT. 

The paper deals with a geometric optimization problem related to graph coloring and minimum cut cover, which suggests that it could belong to the categories of data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of approximation algorithms and complexity results also points towards numerical analysis (cs.NA) and game theory (cs.GT). Finally, the mention of arboricity as a parameter for the performance guarantee of the algorithms suggests that information theory (cs.IT) could also be a relevant category.
